snippet.textDisplay:
This poem alludes to Lord Jesus' incredible sacrifice on the cross as much as it does to JFK's assassination.

I use to think JFK was assassinated because he wanted among other things to take control of the Federal Reserve starting with Executive Order 11110 ... but now I'm not sure. By the way, I don't believe Oswald killed JFK. Check out John Hankey's videos, "Dark Legacy" as well as "Dark Legacy 2" if you'd like to see another perspective.

Anyways. It's hard to pinpoint if Bob Zimmerman ... ehh, "Dylan" ... if Bob Dylan mocks Lord Jesus' sacrifice on the cross, or if Bob Dylan is simply remembering Lord Jesus' sacrifice among other things in this somber poem.

I remember a writing teacher warning me about symbolism. Saying once you start to look for it, symbolism seems to be everywhere including where it isn't. So take that for what it's worth because though I turned in a few good writing assignments during my time in school, I'm no writer. And as Larry the writing teacher would say: A writer writes ... always.

Anyways. One tell of a false-teacher if you will, is they can't help but focus on the suffering and death of Lord Jesus by way of the Garden of Gethsemene, and His scourging, and of course His painful crucifixion. Take note, friends. Lord Jesus went willingly. Not many would choose to go by way of crucifixion.

But focusing on the blood of Lord Jesus, the cross if you will ... is an incomplete understanding of the gospel message. Because the cross means nothing unless Lord Jesus rose from the grave. And Lord Jesus' resurrection means nothing unless He appeared to His closest followers and to hundreds. And some of Lord Jesus' closest followers went to their grave saying they saw the risen Jesus. As well, Lord Jesus' appearances mean nothing unless He ascends. And Lord Jesus' ascencion into Heaven means nothing unless He sends His Holy Spirit which marks the beginning of the church. And the Day of Pentecost means nothing unless people have hope Lord Jesus will return to bring salvation to those who are waiting for Him.

And salvation means among other things, nothing unless it includes the Day of the White Throne Judgement when all those who've rejected Lord Jesus in this life will be given exactly what they've wanted. Because after the White Throne Judgement Lord Jesus will say: It is done.

Remember, the reality of separating yourself from Lord Jesus in this life ... is very different ... than the reality of being separated from Lord Jesus in the next life.

Friends, being like the thief on the cross who is in paradise right now is not the same thing as making it past the White Throne Judgement. Meaning don't wait to cry out to Lord Jesus for forgiveness and help when you are on your proverbial cross. Because today is the day of salvation, not yesterday. And since we are not promised tomorrow, today is the day of salvation.

So I don't pretend to know who will be saved and who won't be saved because I don't know what's in someone's heart. Remember there are false-teachers, and wolves in sheep's clothing who honor Lord Jesus with their lips but their heart is far from Him. So do those people's soul-bodies go to hell or do they go to paradise when they pass away ? ... I don't know.

Matthew 22: v11 thru v13 ... And when the King [Jesus] came in to see the guests, He saw there a man which had not on a wedding garment. Then said the King to the servants: Bind him hand and foot and take him away, and cast him into outer darkness. There shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth. [amen]

Lord have mercy.

Friends, the point of death is important for everyone ... may be even more so for those who've rejected Lord Jesus. Because friends and family of that dying person who also reject Lord Jesus want to see their dying loved one not cry out to Lord Jesus for forgiveness at their proverbial last opportunity. And here's what wiki has Bob saying about making Fire Lake: "The lyric is very ... different ... and very kind of unique. It's about taking risks. About risking love, chucking it all and just heading off with a bunch of wild people, whatever."

W.C. Fields, the famous comedian-actor of the early-1900s, and longtime atheist, and who on his deathbed is reported to have been reading the Holy Bible said he was: Lookin' ferr loopholes, friend ... lookin' ferr loopholes.

The question's not, do you believe in "God" because everybody believes in some kind of God whether that's Lord Jesus or Lucifer, or if they think of themself as God.

So the real question is: In what kind of a God do you believe ?

For those who may not know, Lord Jesus of Nazareth is God. Lord Jesus is not just Son of God, He is Father God.

If you disagree saying Father God has a perfect supernatural will, and Lord Jesus is just human with His separate natural will ? ... understand those two separate wills/natures are in perfect agreement.

If you disagree saying Father God Who is Spirit is a different person than Lord Jesus ? ... so be it. Just know those two different "people" both occupy the same human body named Lord Jesus of Nazareth.

Oldest doctrine in the Holy Bible: God is one and Lord Jesus of Nazareth is God's name.

Man of God. Not woman of God but a man of God who dunks you under water completely declaring exactly, "I baptize you in the name of Jesus Christ for the remission of sins."

Titles baptism: "I baptize you in the name of the Father and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit/Ghost for the remission of sins." Titles baptism is incomplete because it does not use the name of Jesus.

Titles baptism is a modern day equivalent to John the Baptist's baptism. John The Baptist did not baptize using the name of Jesus, so we look to Acts 19: v1 thru v7 to see Paul completing our understanding that water baptism must be performed using the name of Lord Jesus. All the Apostles went out and performed miracles and water-baptisms using the name of Jesus Christ as well.

The only way Matthew 28: v19 and Acts 19: v1 thru v7 and Acts 2: v38 can be reconciled is with the understanding Lord Jesus is Father Jesus. Lord Jesus is Father, Son, and Spirit. Lord Jesus has hundreds of titles, more titles than any other leader in history. Father, Son, and Spirit are just three of Jesus' titles.

Before you go to that man of God, ask him if he knows the difference between titles baptism and baptism in the name of Jesus. If he doesn't then find someone who does. Apostolic Pentecostals know what is proper water baptism in the name of Jesus Christ.

You don't have to consider yourself an Apostolic Pentacostal just because you were water baptized by an Apostolic Pentacostal minister. You are being born again into Lord Jesus and His church, and Apostolic Pentacostal ministers are the few men of God who understand the importance of using the name of Jesus.

Lord Jesus was, is and will always be a Jew Who said follow Him. Lord Jesus never talked about groups or denominations. And it was people in Antioch who first called Lord Jesus' followers Christians. So the first Christians were Jews.

And either before [Acts 10: v44] or after [Acts 19: v6] your water baptism of repentance, you will receive a second and separate Spiritual baptism.

Once you have both water and Spiritual baptisms ... Congratulations, consider yourself born-again of water and Spirit.

When we sin after being water baptized we are to have our feet washed as commanded and demonstrated by Lord Jesus at the Lord's Supper.

snippet.textDisplay: Being one of the many who saw the event on television being aired live, this hit home hard and brought tears to my eyes. It is one of the most prominent memories in my life. I was in second grade and watched it happened when I was home for lunch. I took the news back to class and told the teacher who allowed me to announce it to the classroom. The school let us go to the music room and watch the live funeral and I will wager that there was not a dry eye in that room, student or adult. Things that have come out since then. Well, as you say, murder most foul. This song rings true even though evil and deceit was involved. As a fan of yours since I was in school, I thank you for this wonderful ballad. Many are so oblivious to the truth of it all. Keep writing the truth Mr Dylan.

snippet.textDisplay: I think this is the perfect time to release this song. The JFK assassination was the first time the world was shaken collectively and we found themselves in an incomprehensible descending timeline. But got through it... This is another global trauma that we can rebuild from- Dylan lays out the highlights & lowlights of American culture as a reminder of what is possible, both  good and bad.

snippet.textDisplay: 17:00

Truly awesome stuff! Listen to it 4, 5, 6 times. It's a real "grower". Deliberately slow, like a car crash wherein everything goes slo-mo. It sums up the times then and now. It also sums up the life of JFK, time running out slowly  as the lines of the ballad unfold contrasting the swiftness of the murder itself. Almost as if JFK is seeing it all rushing by as he dies. It's probably one of the saddest songs Bob has ever done.
